<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="10" pageNumber="66" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,679,2005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,679,704]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="66" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dark brown to black with halter black; palpus and base of antenna yellow; frons setose; face with short setae placed medially and transversely; thorax with dark longitudinal bands; legs predominantly yellow, hind pair darker; fore tarsomere 1 not swollen; veins robust, A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[742,750,767,781]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">1</subScript>
long; tergites densely grey pruinose basally and laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,679,2005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,790,815]" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Re-description.</emphasis>
Female. Body 
<quantity box="[555,645,791,815]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="6.3">6.3 mm</quantity>
; wing 
<quantity box="[721,811,791,815]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="6.2">6.2 mm</quantity>
. Head (
<figureCitation box="[898,983,791,815]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
). Dichoptic; ommatidia subequal. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[159,241,826,850]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
) wider than ocellar tubercle, slightly higher than greatest width, slightly divergent near antenna, grey pruinose, except between setae and matte-black eyes, with 8 proclinate setae. Face as high as frons, divergent at ventral margin, grey pruinose with short slender setae, rather inconspicuous, placed medially and transversely. Palpus yellow, slender, with distinct yellow setae. Proboscis (
<figureCitation box="[763,845,935,959]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
) length equal to head height, labrum straight, shiny, yellowish-brown at base, black at apex. Ocellar tubercle slightly protuberant with reddish ocelli, glassy; anterior ocellar seta robust, divergent (damaged) and 3 short posterior setae, aligned. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[1118,1199,1007,1031]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
) yellow, except from distal half of postpedicel velvety matte black; postpedicel around 1.4X longer than length of scape and pedicel combined and around 1.6X longer than three-segmented stylus. Segment 1 of stylus short, segment 2 around 0.5 postpedicel length and 4X longer than thin segment 3. Postcranium (
<figureCitation box="[920,1002,1114,1138]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
) densely grey pruinose; setae of upper half more robust, black; of lower half slender, light yellow. Inner vertical and outer vertical setae slightly longer and more robust than adjacent setae; postocular setae short. Gena and postgena with slender light-yellow setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,679,2005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[297,383,1223,1247]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). Dark brown to black, grey pruinose; postalar callus slightly yellowish-brown; scutum with dark longitudinal band between acrostichal and dorsocentral rows of setae and between dorsocentral and supra-alar rows, latter band wider and contiguous posteriorly. Setae severely damaged, observed from alveoli (most of them not represented in the figure). Chaetotaxy: 3 antepronotals, lateral more robust; 1 robust postpronotals and 8–10 slender; around 6 slender proepisternals, light yellow; more than 15 light yellow slender proepimerals; acrostichals short, misaligned biserial or uniserial; dorsocentrals apparently uniserial, short, except last robust located near postalar callus; some short intra-alar presuturals; intra-alar postsuturals not observed; apparently 3–4 short supra-alar presuturals; 2–3 supra-alar postsuturals, posterior robust; 3 robust notopleurals and several slender; 3 scutellars.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,679,2005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">
Legs (
<figureCitation box="[269,407,1511,1535]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Figs. 63–65</figureCitation>
). Yellow with coxae, hind femora and all tibiae and tarsi dark brown; trochanter with small apical black spot ventrally. Setae short, some of them more robust. Fore tibia (
<figureCitation box="[1039,1122,1546,1570]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
) with 1 anteroventral and 1 apical posteroventral seta. Mid tibia (
<figureCitation box="[578,661,1583,1607]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
) with 3 anteroventral, 4 posteroventral setae on distal half, last two close together. Fore tarsomere 1 not swollen, less than 0.5X length of fore tibia. Hind tibia (
<figureCitation box="[1231,1315,1618,1642]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
) with 4–5 anteroventral setae, last two close together, and 2 dorsal submedially. Tarsomeres with ventral setae more robust.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,679,2005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">
Wing (
<figureCitation box="[278,365,1690,1714]" captionStart="FIGURES 70–75" captionStartId="12.[151,261,579,602]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetId="figure-502@12.[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 70–75. Wings. 70, Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀; 71, H. barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 72, H. carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 73, H. elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂; 74, H. gymnaspis Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 75, H. xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248054/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
). Slightly brown infuscate, veins distinctly black; pterostigma distinct, brown. A 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1296,1304,1706,1720]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">1</subScript>
evanescent only distally. Halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,679,2005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Abdomen dark brown to black, densely grey pruinose more distinct basally and laterally; all tergites grey pruinose in certain angles, notably on last two tergites when viewed anterolaterally; setae clear, small, longer laterally on tergite 1. Posterior tergites with narrow yellow band across hind margin. Sternites dark brown basally, yellowish brown distally; sternite 5 light yellow on posterior margin.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,679,2005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">
Terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[331,465,1909,1933]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Figs. 66–68</figureCitation>
). Tergite 8 with apical sinus and tergite 10 with basal cleft (
<figureCitation box="[1114,1196,1909,1933]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
); cercus short, acuminate distally; sternite 8 more sclerotized laterally, rather acuminate distally. Genital fork subtriangular (
<figureCitation box="[1276,1358,1945,1969]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
). Spermathecal receptacle oval (
<figureCitation box="[439,521,1981,2005]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–69" captionStartId="11.[151,261,1766,1789]" captionTargetBox="[153,1425,853,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-409@11.[151,1436,844,1728]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 58–69. Hilarempis xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru. 58, head, lateral view; 59, postcranium, posterolateral view; 60, frons, frontal view; 61, antenna, lateral view; 62, thorax, dorsal view; 63, right fore leg, posterior view; 64, left mid leg, posterior view; 65, left hind leg, anterior view; 66, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 67, tergite 8, tergite 10 and cercus, dorsal view; 68, sternite 8, sternite 10 and cercus, ventral view; 69, spermathecal receptacle. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, g fk = genital fork, ST = sternite, T = tergite. Scale bars: 58, 62, 63–65 = 1.0 mm; 59–61, = 0.5 mm; 66–68 = 0.2 mm; 69 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248052/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
