<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,788]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,314,404,428]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male 
<typeStatus box="[436,534,404,428]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[719,773,404,427]" name="Peru" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Peru</collectingCountry>
, Callanga was deposited in the Hungarian Natural History Museum and destroyed in 1956 when Russian artillery bombed Budapest. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bezzi, M." box="[970,1171,439,463]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" pagination="298 - 407" refId="ref9061" refString="Bezzi, M. (1909) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der sudamerikanischen Dipterenfauna auf Grund der Sammelergebnisse einer Reise in Chile, Peru und Bolivia, ausgefuhrt in den Jahren 1902 - 1904 von W. Schnuse. Fam. Empididae. Nova Acta Academiae Caesareae Leopoldino-Carolinae Germanicae Naturae Curiosorum, 91, 298 - 407." type="journal article" year="1909">Bezzi (1909: 367)</bibRefCitation>
described a conspecific female specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[403,457,476,499]" name="Peru" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Peru</collectingCountry>
, Pichisweg, and this specimen is re-described here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,788]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis box="[199,332,511,536]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,511,536]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Discussion</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The male 
<typeStatus box="[451,549,511,535]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1905" box="[586,844,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocera">
<emphasis box="[586,844,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Hilarempis xanthocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described as dichoptic (
<emphasis box="[1281,1348,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">oculis</emphasis>
s 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">ejunctis</emphasis>
). Besides this character the thorax is dark ground-colour, antenna yellow and mesonotum with four dark bands. These characters take this species to couplet 13 of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Philippi, 1865)" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[717,1062,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrozona">
<emphasis box="[717,878,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">H. argyrozona</emphasis>
(Philippi, 1865)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Collin, J. E." box="[1098,1268,583,607]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" refId="ref9118" refString="Collin, J. E. (1933) Empididae. Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile. Volume 4, London, British Museum of Natural History, London. Vol. 4, 334 pp., 74 figs." type="book" year="1933">Collin’s (1933)</bibRefCitation>
key. The latter species was re-described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Collin, J. E." box="[476,633,620,644]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" refId="ref9118" refString="Collin, J. E. (1933) Empididae. Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile. Volume 4, London, British Museum of Natural History, London. Vol. 4, 334 pp., 74 figs." type="book" year="1933">Collin (1933)</bibRefCitation>
. Both species have cell dm slightly produced (
<figureCitation box="[1165,1250,620,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 70–75" captionStartId="12.[151,261,579,602]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetId="figure-502@12.[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 70–75. Wings. 70, Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀; 71, H. barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 72, H. carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 73, H. elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂; 74, H. gymnaspis Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 75, H. xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248054/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
). They differ by ocellar setae robust (small, no longer and hardly stronger than short setae on frons in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[1146,1310,657,680]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrozona">
<emphasis box="[1146,1310,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">H. argyrozona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), antennae entirely yellow (postpedicel black in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[570,732,693,716]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrozona">
<emphasis box="[570,732,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">H. argyrozona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), legs with hind femur and all tibiae dark brown (yellowish in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[151,315,729,752]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrozona">
<emphasis box="[151,315,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">H. argyrozona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The examined specimen is female and not possible to compare with genitalia figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Collin, J. E." pageId="11" pageNumber="67" refId="ref9118" refString="Collin, J. E. (1933) Empididae. Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile. Volume 4, London, British Museum of Natural History, London. Vol. 4, 334 pp., 74 figs." type="book" year="1933">Collin (1933)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
